Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} and pepper to the pan. Use a #spoon to mash the burgers into a mince-like texture as it cooks. Cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g}, @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} and @water{2%tbsp}(for the sauce) to the pan. Cook, stirring to combine, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @BBQ sauce{32%g} into the pan and mix well.

Season with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

== Assembly ==

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per person) onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{}.

Spoon the plant-based burger filling onto one half of each tortilla and top with the cheese.

Fold the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Rub each quesadilla with a little oil, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once ready, transfer the quesadillas to your plates.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} on the side.

Serve the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} alongside for dipping. Enjoy!